UGHELLI – Former Governors of Delta State, Chief James Onanefe Ibori and Dr Emmanuel Uduaghan will on Saturday, March 19, 2022, attend the official declaration ceremony of Chief Ighoyota Amori to contest for the Delta Central Senatorial District seat come 2023 as Special Guest of Honour and Guest of Honour respectively. In a statement signed by the Chairman, Publicity Committee of ‘Amori for Senate 2023’, Olorogun Arthur Akpowowo, stated that the ceremony will begin at 10 am at the Mosogar Country Home of Senator Chief Ighoyota Amori and will be chaired by former Commissioner for Higher Education in Delta State, Prof. Hope Eghagha. According to the statement, political juggernauts, leaders of thought, youths, women, community leaders from all walks of life especially from Delta Central Senatorial District are expected to be in attendance.